gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 134, Hawks 112
gameRecap.excerpt: The Warriors defeated the Hawks, 134-112. Stephen Curry (25 points, eight assists, five 3PT) and Jonathan Kuminga (25 points, 11-11 FG, nine rebounds) and Klay Thompson (24 points, 5-10 3PT) totaled 74 points as the Warriors had seven players in double-figures overall. Dejounte Murray led the Hawks with 23 points, seven rebounds, and seven assists as Jalen Johnson added 21 points, nine rebounds, and six assists. The Warriors improve to 19-22 as the Hawks move to 18-26.
